## Rules

- Preserve the user's intent, order, constraints, and risks. Do not invent commands, environments, platforms, services, scripts, or deployment targets.
- If no name is provided, `title` must be a short title generated from the new input. If a name is provided, keep it or lightly normalize it.
- Write "To confirm" when information is missing.
- Use only these sections: `Applicability`, `Inputs And Prerequisites`, `Steps`, `Validation`, `Risks And Rollback`.
- Use an ordered list for `Steps`; write natural-language steps when commands are not confirmed.
- Do not output a `Scripts` section; skills-seed generates the script index.
- In append mode, merge and deduplicate; put conflicts in `suggestions`.

## Output

Return JSON only, no code fence. Shape example:

```json
{
  "title": "Short title",
  "summary": "One-sentence summary",
  "content": "# Title\n\n## Applicability\n...\n\n## Inputs And Prerequisites\n...\n\n## Steps\n1. ...\n\n## Validation\n...\n\n## Risks And Rollback\n...\n",
  "suggestions": ["Gaps or conflicts"]
}
```
